<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 28</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Object name</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="ece0aab2-b130-44fc-b26b-4d4e88cf266f">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 29</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Object role</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="66b93376-2ef6-4712-a771-b4d599ba19cf">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 30</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Object value or state depending on events</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="53524838-14c1-482b-a459-55c2f2acb5e6">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 31</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>App module</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="81183c80-fbca-4172-b892-61c4ae72a759">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 32</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>For IAccessible objects: acc name, child ID</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="ce186188-5500-4498-a707-6df906d9380d">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 33</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>For UIA objects: Automation Id, class name, notification properties if recording notification event information, child count for layout invalidated event, properties for item status, drag drop, and drop target effect if defined</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="288fdd32-6365-4057-842f-3d5089fe29b0">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 35</note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>You can also assign a gesture to view the events on a list (NVDA menu/Preferences/Input gestures, Event Tracker category). The list saves up to 100 latest events processed prior to opening the dialog.</source>
</segment>
</unit>
